- **bottleneck-exponent-dns.md** — **NEW (E002).** Bottleneck exponent gamma (I_k ~ U_{k-1}^gamma) for the pressure integral P_k^{21}. Gamma DECREASES with Re for ALL ICs. At Re>=500, most ICs show gamma < 1. ABC maintains gamma > 1.1 (Beltrami structure). **E009: DNS evidence cannot diagnose near-singular bounds; gap genuineness supported by analytical/sociological evidence, not DNS.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED]
