# Vasseur De Giorgi Framework — Navier-Stokes

Vasseur's 2007 De Giorgi approach to Navier-Stokes partial regularity (NoDEA 14:753-785). The framework defines a nonlinear recurrence U_k <= C^k * U_{k-1}^{beta_p} on level set energy quantities. The exponent beta_p controls regularity: beta > 1 gives partial regularity (CKN), beta > 3/2 would give full regularity. Current proof achieves beta < 4/3. The bottleneck is a single term: the non-divergence part of the local pressure P_k^{21}. **28 entries.** (NEW: vasseur-pressure S2-E008 — **Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields** (constant field u=(c,0,0) achieves ratio->1); all 4 De Giorgi chain steps individually confirmed tight under NS constraints; beta = 4/3 SHARP (rigorous) within De Giorgi-Vasseur framework; SDP formalization unnecessary — analytic extremizer is elementary; open question from S2-E001/S2-E003 (div-free level-set distribution) RESOLVED; 4 existing entries updated. Prior: S2-E007 adversarial review, S2-E006 non-CZ pressure routes, S2-E005 LP obstruction, S2-E002 DNS level-set distribution, S2-E004 compensated compactness, S2-E003 Chebyshev universality, S2-E001 sharpness audit, E010 near-Beltrami definitive negative, E009 adversarial, E007 Beltrami deficit truncation, E008 vorticity/H^1, E005 CV14, E006 Beltrami, E004 CZ slack.)

## Entries

- **beta-definition-recurrence-exponent.md** — Beta is the nonlinear recurrence exponent in the De Giorgi iteration (NOT a pressure integrability exponent). Defined via Proposition 3 (equation (5)). Beta > 1 suffices for partial regularity via Lemma 4. [VERIFIED]
- **beta-threshold-three-halves.md** — Beta > 3/2 implies ALL suitable weak solutions are regular. Proved in Vasseur's Appendix via rescaled NS equations. Conjecture 14 states this threshold is achievable. The value 3/2 is the natural scale of 3D NS in the De Giorgi framework. [VERIFIED]
- **beta-current-value-four-thirds.md** — Current best beta < 4/3. Bottleneck is the non-divergence local pressure term P_k^{21}, with exponent 4/3 - 5/(3q) -> 4/3 as q -> inf. All other terms achieve 5/3 (well above 3/2). Gap of 1/6 is qualitative, not perturbative. Four possible routes to close the gap identified. [VERIFIED]
- **de-giorgi-iteration-structure.md** — The 7-step De Giorgi iteration procedure: level sets, evolution equation, cutoff integration, Sobolev+Chebyshev power raising, bottleneck identification, nonlinear recurrence, convergence lemma. Beta enters at Step 4 as the minimum over all term exponents. [VERIFIED]
- **dns-beta-measurement.md** — Three approaches for empirically measuring beta from DNS: direct iteration measurement (fit U_k recurrence) **[TESTED E002]**, bottleneck term measurement (isolate P_k^{21} integral) **[TESTED E002]**, CZ slack proxy **[TESTED E004, ELIMINATED]**. Partially computable: ~10-15 De Giorgi levels on a 512^3 grid. Answer: empirical beta does NOT exceed 4/3 for any tested case. [PROVISIONAL → partially VERIFIED]
- **dns-beta-empirical-results.md** — **NEW (E002).** Full DNS measurement results: 5 ICs x 4 Re x 2 resolutions. All beta_eff < 4/3 (max 1.01 for ABC at Re=1000). Strong IC dependence: ABC (0.90-1.01) >> RandomGauss (0.35-0.39). Critical caveat: beta_eff != beta_p (different quantities). **E009: smooth-solution tautology — beta_eff < 4/3 is expected for smooth flows and proves nothing about analytical bound tightness. Measurement survives as empirical fact; interpretation does NOT.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED]
- **bottleneck-exponent-dns.md** — **NEW (E002).** Bottleneck exponent gamma (I_k ~ U_{k-1}^gamma) for the pressure integral P_k^{21}. Gamma DECREASES with Re for ALL ICs. At Re>=500, most ICs show gamma < 1. ABC maintains gamma > 1.1 (Beltrami structure). **E009: DNS evidence cannot diagnose near-singular bounds; gap genuineness supported by analytical/sociological evidence, not DNS.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED]
- **abc-beltrami-degiorgi-advantage.md** — **NEW (E002), UPDATED (E009, E010).** ABC (Beltrami) flow: highest beta_eff (1.01), best R^2 (0.999), most stable gamma (1.10-1.22), smallest U_0 (~270). **E009: strongest surviving finding is the structural story. E010: advantage is measure-zero specific — beta_eff degrades continuously with perturbation (1.01 at eps=0 -> 0.89 at eps=0.05 -> 0.28 at eps=0.50).** [VERIFIED]
- **cz-slack-k-independent.md** — **NEW (E004).** CZ tightness ratio for P_k^{21} converges to a k-independent constant by k ~ 3-4. FALSIFIES hypothesis that CZ slack could improve beta. **E009: measurement on wrong regime — smooth flows, not near-singular. Survives as empirical fact, not as evidence about analytical bound tightness.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED]
- **p21-tighter-than-full-pressure.md** — **NEW (E004).** P_k^{21} has LESS CZ slack than the full pressure: 1.7-3.9x vs 7.6-17.5x at q=2. The bottleneck piece's RHS tensor (u_below x u_below) is smoother/more structured. P22 and P23 have progressively more slack. CZ bound is tightest precisely where it matters most. Pressure decomposition verified to machine precision (<1.1e-15). [VERIFIED]
- **tran-yu-galilean-invariance-orthogonal.md** — **NEW (E003).** Tran-Yu program (5 papers, 2015-2021) on pressure moderation and Galilean invariance is ORTHOGONAL to De Giorgi bottleneck. Different energy functionals (global L^q vs level-set), different pressure objects (full p vs P_k^{21}), Galilean boost doesn't help P_k^{21}. Classification: better constant only, not better exponent. Grade C (not applicable). Two potentially useful ideas: nonlinear depletion at velocity maxima, velocity-pressure anti-correlation. [VERIFIED]
- **pressure-galilean-invariance.md** — **NEW (E003).** Pressure Poisson equation is exactly Galilean-invariant for incompressible flow (div u = 0 kills cross-terms). CZ bound ||p||_{L^q} <= C_q||u||_{L^{2q}}^2 unchanged by any constant-velocity frame shift. Fundamental reason Galilean boosts cannot improve the CZ bound on P_k^{21}. [VERIFIED]
- **choi-vasseur-2014-decomposition.md** — **NEW (E005).** Choi-Vasseur (2014, AIHP) three-way decomposition P = P_{1,k} + P_{2,k} + P_3 with P_3 absorbed into time-dependent truncation level. Achieves beta = 7/6 (weaker than 4/3, sufficient for their purpose). Does NOT bypass P_k^{21} bottleneck — the local pressure P_{2,k} still contains the CZ-limited non-divergence term. Technical simplification, not exponent improvement. [VERIFIED]
- **post-2007-beta-landscape.md** — **NEW (E005).** Comprehensive survey: NO paper since 2007 has attempted or claimed to improve beta beyond 4/3 in De Giorgi NS iteration. Community moved orthogonally: higher derivatives (CV14, Vasseur-Yang 2021), alternative regularity frameworks (epsilon-regularity, concentration), and extensions to other equations. The 4/3 barrier is untouched. [VERIFIED]
- **fernandez-dalgo-2025-dynamic-pressure.md** — **NEW (E005).** Fernandez-Dalgo (arXiv:2501.18402v2, April 2025) introduces time-dependent pressure decomposition in paraboloid geometry. Uses Gronwall-type energy methods, NOT De Giorgi iteration. About epsilon-regularity criteria, not the recurrence exponent beta. [PROVISIONAL]
- **vorticity-degiorgi-universal-barrier.md** — **NEW (E008).** Vasseur-Yang (2021) applies De Giorgi iteration to pressure-free variable v. New 4/3 bottleneck from trilinear form (1/2 + 5/6 = 4/3), independent of pressure. **E009: "universality" is induction from 2 examples, not theorem — but two independent mechanisms both hitting 4/3 is suggestive. Proof of universality remains open.** [VERIFIED, clarified]
- **h1-pressure-dead-end.md** — **NEW (E008, philosopher-atlas).** Three H^1 routes to improving beta (H^1-BMO duality, atomic decomposition, complex interpolation) all fail at the W^{1,3} wall. beta = 3/2 and W^{1,3} are two faces of the same obstruction. Far-field pressure is the sole obstruction (local closes). H^1 norm of pressure is a fixed constant (total kinetic energy). Structural dead end: do NOT pursue H^1-based improvements. [VERIFIED]
- **beltrami-deficit-truncation-survival.md** — **NEW (E007), UPDATED (E009, E010).** De Giorgi truncation u_below preserves Beltrami structure: B_k = O(2^{-k}). **E009: DOES NOT SURVIVE AS STATED. E010: DEFINITIVELY CONFIRMED — perturbed-ABC (eps=0.01-0.50) shows B_k plateaus for any eps > 0; beta > 1 only for eps < ~0.02; Leray projection minor correction. WEAKEST CLAIM in Strategy-001, now closed.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED, CLOSED by E010]
- **pressure-bernoulli-dominance-truncated.md** — **NEW (E007), UPDATED (E009, E010).** Truncated pressure for ABC is Bernoulli-dominated: R_frac = O(2^{-k}). **E009: shares Claim 5 limitations. E010: near-Beltrami now characterized — Bernoulli dominance lost for eps >= 0.05 (R_floor = 7.3%); R > 1 at eps=0.50. Open questions answered: NO generalization.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED, CLOSED by E010]
- **proposition-3-sharpness-audit.md** — **NEW (S2-E001).** Line-by-line sharpness audit of Vasseur (2007) Proposition 3: complete sensitivity table (8 steps, dβ/dδ for each), 5/6 genealogy (H^1→L^6→L^{10/3}→Chebyshev→L^2), all 5 free parameters exhausted (truncation, Sobolev target, Holder pairs, pressure decomposition, cutoffs). Single potentially improvable step: Chebyshev inequality applied to NS solutions (sharp for arbitrary L^{10/3} functions, potentially loose for NS). Three improvement directions ranked. Vorticity cross-comparison confirms identical chain. [VERIFIED]
- **chebyshev-universality-and-model-pde-comparison.md** — **NEW (S2-E003).** Universal formula beta = 1 + s/n for De Giorgi recursion exponent (Brigati-Mouhot 2025 confirms). Verified across 9 model PDEs: Burgers (beta=2), 2D NS (3/2), 3D NS (4/3), 4D NS (5/4), MHD (4/3), SQG direct (5/4), SQG extension (4/3), fractional NS alpha=5/4 (17/12), fractional NS alpha=3/2 (3/2). Chebyshev step NOT independently improvable — 6 routes ruled out or circular (improving L^{10/3} to L^4 requires H^{5/4} = Lions threshold). SQG success mechanism: drift is multiplicative (BMO^{-1} constant), not additional U power; commutator structure, not Chebyshev improvement. Open question: does div(u)=0 improve level-set distribution? (no paper addresses; appears genuinely open). MHD confirmed beta=4/3 (He-Xin 2005). Fractional NS: De Giorgi misses Lions regularity by alpha gap (5/4 vs 3/2). [VERIFIED]
