 ## Entries
 
 - **beta-definition-recurrence-exponent.md** — Beta is the nonlinear recurrence exponent in the De Giorgi iteration (NOT a pressure integrability exponent). Defined via Proposition 3 (equation (5)). Beta > 1 suffices for partial regularity via Lemma 4. [VERIFIED]
 - **beta-threshold-three-halves.md** — Beta > 3/2 implies ALL suitable weak solutions are regular. Proved in Vasseur's Appendix via rescaled NS equations. Conjecture 14 states this threshold is achievable. The value 3/2 is the natural scale of 3D NS in the De Giorgi framework. [VERIFIED]
 - **beta-current-value-four-thirds.md** — Current best beta < 4/3. Bottleneck is the non-divergence local pressure term P_k^{21}, with exponent 4/3 - 5/(3q) -> 4/3 as q -> inf. All other terms achieve 5/3 (well above 3/2). Gap of 1/6 is qualitative, not perturbative. Four possible routes to close the gap identified. [VERIFIED]
+- **exact-far-field-pressure-obstruction.md** — Exact reconstruction of the surviving "far-field harmonic loophole": Vasseur's harmonic term `P_{k1}` is already favorable; the bad slot is local `P_{k21}`. The only live loophole is an alternative near/far decomposition that recaptures part of the dangerous local interaction and makes the pressure factor `U_k`-dependent. [VERIFIED]
 - **de-giorgi-iteration-structure.md** — The 7-step De Giorgi iteration procedure: level sets, evolution equation, cutoff integration, Sobolev+Chebyshev power raising, bottleneck identification, nonlinear recurrence, convergence lemma. Beta enters at Step 4 as the minimum over all term exponents. [VERIFIED]
 - **dns-beta-measurement.md** — Three approaches for empirically measuring beta from DNS: direct iteration measurement (fit U_k recurrence) **[TESTED E002]**, bottleneck term measurement (isolate P_k^{21} integral) **[TESTED E002]**, CZ slack proxy **[TESTED E004, ELIMINATED]**. Partially computable: ~10-15 De Giorgi levels on a 512^3 grid. Answer: empirical beta does NOT exceed 4/3 for any tested case. [PROVISIONAL → partially VERIFIED]
 - **dns-beta-empirical-results.md** — **NEW (E002).** Full DNS measurement results: 5 ICs x 4 Re x 2 resolutions. All beta_eff < 4/3 (max 1.01 for ABC at Re=1000). Strong IC dependence: ABC (0.90-1.01) >> RandomGauss (0.35-0.39). Critical caveat: beta_eff != beta_p (different quantities). **E009: smooth-solution tautology — beta_eff < 4/3 is expected for smooth flows and proves nothing about analytical bound tightness. Measurement survives as empirical fact; interpretation does NOT.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED]
@@ -20,7 +21,7 @@
 - **post-2007-beta-landscape.md** — **NEW (E005).** Comprehensive survey: NO paper since 2007 has attempted or claimed to improve beta beyond 4/3 in De Giorgi NS iteration. Community moved orthogonally: higher derivatives (CV14, Vasseur-Yang 2021), alternative regularity frameworks (epsilon-regularity, concentration), and extensions to other equations. The 4/3 barrier is untouched. [VERIFIED]
