 # Vasseur De Giorgi Framework — Navier-Stokes
 
-Vasseur's 2007 De Giorgi approach to Navier-Stokes partial regularity (NoDEA 14:753-785). The framework defines a nonlinear recurrence U_k <= C^k * U_{k-1}^{beta_p} on level set energy quantities. The exponent beta_p controls regularity: beta > 1 gives partial regularity (CKN), beta > 3/2 would give full regularity. Current proof achieves beta < 4/3. The bottleneck is a single term: the non-divergence part of the local pressure P_k^{21}. **28 entries.** (NEW: vasseur-pressure S2-E008 — **Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields** (constant field u=(c,0,0) achieves ratio->1); all 4 De Giorgi chain steps individually confirmed tight under NS constraints; beta = 4/3 SHARP (rigorous) within De Giorgi-Vasseur framework; SDP formalization unnecessary — analytic extremizer is elementary; open question from S2-E001/S2-E003 (div-free level-set distribution) RESOLVED; 4 existing entries updated. Prior: S2-E007 adversarial review, S2-E006 non-CZ pressure routes, S2-E005 LP obstruction, S2-E002 DNS level-set distribution, S2-E004 compensated compactness, S2-E003 Chebyshev universality, S2-E001 sharpness audit, E010 near-Beltrami definitive negative, E009 adversarial, E007 Beltrami deficit truncation, E008 vorticity/H^1, E005 CV14, E006 Beltrami, E004 CZ slack.)
